    excerpt: "Baby Eating Hands? What's Normal and When to Worry ! Key Takeaways Babies chewing/sucking on their hands is a normal developmental behavior: The article explains that around 2-3 months of age, babies start exploring their environment and developing hand-eye coordination, which often involves putting their hands in their mouths. This behavior is a typical part [&hellip;]",
