    title: "6 Month Milestones: Tracking Your Baby's Development and what to avoid.",
    excerpt: "Babies often experience a variety of physical, cognitive, and social milestones throughout their first six months of life. In terms of physical development, your baby could be able to roll over from their stomach to their back and elevate their head and chest while lying on their stomach. Additionally, they might be able to sit [&hellip;]",
    date: "",
    category: "Milestones",
